Buckle up, full cirlce moment here: 2017 I graduated Plymouth State University with $60,000 in student loan debt. The bank said I would pay $285 a month for the next 10 years and then I’d be debt free! (they said with a smile) as if that was “good news”…I was pissed. 

At that moment in life I felt trapped, like I couldn’t breathe with all this debt around me. I was dead broke, living with my parents, and ungodly single…I knew I was capable of much more. 

It was at that moment I sold my first couch that was gifted to my family from a neighbor. I think I made $180 from that 1st sale. I was hooked. I thought DAMN if I just had a million more couches I could pay off this debt. 

That same year I bump into Gary Vee in an airport and told him how I just sold my first couch. “Respect” he said as we bro hugged lol (snapped a quick selfie..see second pic) 

My saying was “a couch a day keeps the student loans away”..I picked up and or sold 1 couch a day for 2 years straight. I paid that student loan debt off in 2 years after graduating all because I saw a guy on the Internet going to garage sales and flipping mugs…

Own your sh*t, and take massive action. Only you can help you 

Thank you G @garyvee
